WEBVTT

00:01.285 --> 00:02.626
Sheila Amanda Sazs,

00:02.651 --> 00:04.005
will you marry me?

00:04.006 --> 00:06.041
Yes, I will marry you.

00:06.108 --> 00:07.309
- I want to go legit.
- You can't.

00:07.376 --> 00:09.244
Then I get Lola Jensen
to hack into the bar

00:09.312 --> 00:11.313
and just put me in there,
just like she did with Harvard.

00:11.380 --> 00:12.914
Rule number one
of not getting caught,

00:12.982 --> 00:14.516
you don't move
the goddamn body.

00:14.583 --> 00:16.384
Harvey, I'm stuck.

00:16.452 --> 00:18.620
I can't live my whole life
like this.

00:18.688 --> 00:20.655
You want me to set up
your new corporation?

00:20.723 --> 00:23.024
I want you to join
my new corporation.

00:23.092 --> 00:25.560
We're not lawyers.
We're investment bankers.

00:25.628 --> 00:27.529
Our job blows yours
out of the water.

00:27.596 --> 00:30.598
Scottie, I need you to give
Louis his transaction back.

00:30.666 --> 00:33.501
Does this have something to do
with that favor he did you?

00:33.569 --> 00:36.571
- Yes.
- Tell me what it is.

00:36.639 --> 00:37.839
- I can't.
- Guess we're not sharing

00:37.907 --> 00:39.507
everything with each other
after all.

00:39.575 --> 00:40.742
- Scottie.
- You can't have it

00:40.810 --> 00:42.243
both ways, Harvey.

00:42.311 --> 00:44.579
- Louis, I don't want kids.
- What are you talking about?

00:44.647 --> 00:46.114
I don't like kids.

00:46.182 --> 00:49.017
I was willing to give up Harvard
for you.

00:49.085 --> 00:51.453
You can't give up something
for me?

00:57.927 --> 01:00.395
I understand.
Can I just say something please?

01:00.463 --> 01:04.666
I know you keep saying that
I won't feel this way forever,

01:04.733 --> 01:07.902
but why is it
when the guys shows up

01:07.970 --> 01:09.671
with chicken vindaloo
40 minutes late

01:09.739 --> 01:12.674
with no naan
and no silverware,

01:12.742 --> 01:14.709
instead of throwing the chutney
in his face,

01:14.777 --> 01:17.679
I'm thanking him
and I am tipping him $20?

01:17.747 --> 01:21.783
Do you want to tell me
why that happens?

01:21.851 --> 01:24.352
I don't care.
I hate myself.

01:24.420 --> 01:26.187
I hate my life.

01:26.255 --> 01:28.456
The woman I love is gone,
my heart is broken,

01:28.524 --> 01:29.991
and I really--
to be honest with you,

01:30.059 --> 01:31.826
I just don't have
the will to live.

01:31.894 --> 01:34.863
[Beeps]

01:34.930 --> 01:37.699
Hold on.
It's my associate.

01:37.767 --> 01:38.767
Katrina.

01:38.834 --> 01:40.769
Louis, it's 7:55.

01:40.836 --> 01:42.170
Yeah.
I have an 8:00 a.m.

01:42.238 --> 01:44.706
Please cover it for me.
In fact, cover everything,

01:44.774 --> 01:46.941
and unless the building
is on fire and Sheila's in it,

01:47.009 --> 01:48.843
I'm not coming in.
Louis, what happened?

01:48.911 --> 01:50.044
You wanna know what happened?
I'll tell you what happened.

01:50.112 --> 01:51.212
My heart's been shattered

01:51.280 --> 01:52.520
into a thousand million pieces,

01:52.581 --> 01:54.015
and if I can't put my heart
into my work,

01:54.083 --> 01:56.418
then I'm not gonna do
any work at all, so...

01:56.485 --> 01:58.253
How long do you think
you'll be out?

01:58.320 --> 01:59.854
I don't know.
Today, tomorrow,

01:59.922 --> 02:01.356
the rest of the year.

02:01.424 --> 02:02.624
You know,
just don't call here again

02:02.691 --> 02:05.827
because I'm not gonna answer
the number.

02:05.895 --> 02:08.596
Doc?

02:08.663 --> 02:11.199
Dr. Lipschitz?

02:11.267 --> 02:13.835
Hello?

02:13.903 --> 02:16.838
What, are you shitting me?
That was not 50 minutes.

02:18.000 --> 02:24.074
Advertise your product or brand here
contact www.OpenSubtitles.org today

02:31.020 --> 02:33.688
Waiting outside for me?
Bold gesture.

02:33.756 --> 02:36.090
I called you three times.
I had to do something.

02:36.158 --> 02:38.293
- You must be feeling bad.
- I am.

02:38.360 --> 02:42.497
What for?
You're just doing your job.

02:42.565 --> 02:44.999
Scottie, I'm sorry.

02:45.067 --> 02:47.702
What happened with Louis,
I didn't like doing it.

02:47.770 --> 02:49.904
- Yeah, but you still did it.
- And what I'm doing now

02:49.972 --> 02:51.539
is asking you to let it go.

02:51.607 --> 02:53.308
Harvey, it's not that you
picked Louis over me.

02:53.375 --> 02:54.742
It's that you wouldn't
tell me why.

02:54.810 --> 02:57.645
I couldn't tell you why.
There's a difference.

02:57.713 --> 03:02.917
And I'm asking you
to trust me.

03:02.985 --> 03:05.487
Okay.

03:05.554 --> 03:08.556
I can let it go,
but keeping things from me

03:08.624 --> 03:12.360
just can't keep happening,
okay?

03:12.428 --> 03:14.496
I can't tell you
whether or not that's okay,

03:14.563 --> 03:19.200
and I definitely
can't tell you why.

03:19.268 --> 03:20.935
Too soon?

03:21.003 --> 03:22.637
What are you going to do
to make it up to me?

03:22.705 --> 03:24.172
Nothing right now.

03:24.240 --> 03:26.674
I'm taking Mike
to the marathon footwear brunch.

03:26.742 --> 03:28.303
You're taking a date
to an I.P.O. event?

03:28.344 --> 03:29.911
That's so cute.
It's not a date.

03:29.979 --> 03:31.346
He's never gonna put out.

03:31.413 --> 03:32.747
Well, it's too bad
that you're not taking me

03:32.815 --> 03:35.650
because I was thinking
of letting you...

03:35.718 --> 03:38.653
[Whispers indistinctly]

03:43.926 --> 03:46.928
Mr. Specter.

03:46.996 --> 03:48.329
James Quelling.

03:48.397 --> 03:50.198
I'm in a bit of a hurry,
Mr. quelling.

03:50.266 --> 03:52.700
- I want to do you a favor.
- I don't need any favors.

03:52.768 --> 03:55.537
Yeah, you do, unless you want
Friday's headline to read,

03:55.604 --> 03:58.540
"Marathon Footwear builds
playgrounds that kill children."

03:58.607 --> 04:00.341
My client builds playgrounds
that help children.

04:00.409 --> 04:03.444
And uses a synthetic
full of toxins to do it.

04:03.512 --> 04:05.547
Look, I don't know
who you are,

04:05.614 --> 04:08.014
but I know what you're trying
to do, and it isn't gonna work.

04:08.017 --> 04:09.450
Look,
I'm a reasonable man.

04:09.518 --> 04:11.419
This is a huge moment
for your client.

04:11.487 --> 04:13.621
I won't file this
before Friday.

04:13.689 --> 04:15.990
You think I'm gonna let you
extort my client?

04:16.058 --> 04:18.593
No, I think you're gonna
protect your client

04:18.661 --> 04:20.461
from a claim
that could ruin them.

04:20.529 --> 04:25.567
In fact,
I'm counting on it.

04:25.634 --> 04:27.902
Nice offices.
Enjoy that brunch.

04:30.072 --> 04:32.740
- I got a job offer.
- Holy shit. From who?

04:32.808 --> 04:34.375
Last night.
Jonathan Sidwell.

04:34.443 --> 04:36.377
But I thought Louis
was his lawyer.

04:36.445 --> 04:38.513
He doesn't want me
to be his lawyer.

04:38.581 --> 04:42.183
He wants me to be a partner.

04:42.251 --> 04:44.352
- Investment banking?
- Yeah.

04:44.420 --> 04:45.720
- And?
- I don't know.

04:45.788 --> 04:46.988
- What do you think?
- I don't know.

04:47.056 --> 04:49.724
What do you think?
I think that I love you,

04:49.792 --> 04:53.695
and what you want to do
is what I want you to do.

04:53.762 --> 04:55.763
I don't know what to do.

04:55.831 --> 04:58.299
Okay.
Did you talk to Harvey?

04:58.367 --> 05:00.168
If I do that,
all he'll hear is, "Hey, Harvey,

05:00.169 --> 05:01.302
"thanks for doing everything
for me.

05:01.370 --> 05:03.137
I'm thinking about quitting."
Well...

05:03.205 --> 05:04.639
No, but you said
that you don't think of him

05:04.707 --> 05:06.474
as just your boss.
You consider him a friend.

05:06.542 --> 05:08.543
- So?
- So if he can't have

05:08.611 --> 05:11.813
an honest conversation with
your best interests in mind,

05:11.880 --> 05:15.717
he's not your friend, and--
and he shouldn't be your boss.

05:18.621 --> 05:22.290
♪ See the money,
wanna stay for your meal ♪

05:22.358 --> 05:25.593
♪ get another piece of pie
for your wife ♪

05:25.661 --> 05:28.763
♪ everybody wanna know
how it feel ♪

05:28.831 --> 05:32.533
♪ everybody wanna see
what it's like ♪

05:32.601 --> 05:35.570
♪ living in a beehive
of your mind ♪

05:35.638 --> 05:39.440
<font color=#00FF00>♪ Suits 3x15 ♪</font>
<font color=#00FFFF>Know When to Fold 'Em</font>
